<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<B><FONT SIZE="+1">Statistics 101: Midterm Exam 1</FONT></B>
</DIV>
<P>
<B>Problem I</B>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT><B>A.</B>
<DD>Since the distance from the median to lower quartile
<I>Q</I><SUB>1</SUB> is less than the distance from the median to the upper
quartile <I>Q</I><SUB>3</SUB> this indicates the number of hits is skewed to the
right. Also the lower whisker is smaller than the upper whisker.
<DT><B>B.</B>
<DD>Visually 36 is not above the upper whisker.
Also 
<!-- MATH: $IQR=Q_3-Q_1=19-2=17$ -->
<I>IQR</I>=<I>Q</I><SUB>3</SUB>-<I>Q</I><SUB>1</SUB>=19-2=17 and the upper inner fence is

<!-- MATH: $Q_3+1.5*IQR=44.5$ -->
<I>Q</I><SUB>3</SUB>+1.5*<I>IQR</I>=44.5. Since 36 is smaller it is not a candidate
outlier.
<DT><B>C.</B>
<DD>The median is higher for recreational than for
business. Since the box is bigger for recreational it also has
higher variance. Business and recreational are both skewed to the
right.
<DT><B>D.</B>
<DD>Since 36 is well above the box for business it would
be candidate outlier. Visually 
<!-- MATH: $Q_3\sim 12$ -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="61" HEIGHT="29" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img1.gif"
 ALT="$Q_3\sim 12$">
and 
<!-- MATH: $IQR\sim 12$ -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="74" HEIGHT="29" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img2.gif"
 ALT="$IQR\sim 12$">.
So
limit is 
<!-- MATH: $12+1.5*12=30$ -->
12+1.5*12=30.
<DT><B>E.</B>
<DD><DT><B>(i)</B>
<DD>The right tail would be pulled in (higher values
less extreme). This would make the data look symmetric.
<DT><B>(ii)</B>
<DD>Since logs preserve order, median of the

<!-- MATH: $\ln (\mbox{ hits }) =\ln(7.5)=2.0149$ -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="199" HEIGHT="31" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img3.gif"
 ALT="$\ln (\mbox{ hits }) =\ln(7.5)=2.0149$">.
</DL>
<P>
<B>Problem II</B>

<P>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT><B>A.</B>
<DD>Because  <I>B</I> and <I>C</I> are independent, it follows
that
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH: \begin{displaymath}
{\bf P}(A\cup C)={\bf P}(B)+{\bf P}(C)-{\bf P}(B\cap C)={\bf P}(B)+{\bf P}(C)- {\bf P}(B)*{\bf P}(C)
=.5+.4-.5*.4=.7.
\end{displaymath} -->

<IMG
 WIDTH="588" HEIGHT="38"
 SRC="img5.gif"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}{\bf P}(A\cup C)={\bf P}(B)+{\bf P}(C)-{\bf P}(B\cap C)={\bf P}(B)+{\bf P}(C)- {\bf P}(B)*{\bf P}(C)
=.5+.4-.5*.4=.7.\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P><DT><B>B.</B>
<DD>Since <IMG
 WIDTH="47" HEIGHT="15" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img6.gif"
 ALT="$B\cap A$">
is a subset of <IMG
 WIDTH="47" HEIGHT="15" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img7.gif"
 ALT="$B\cup C$">
we get that
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH: \begin{displaymath}
{\bf P}(B\cap C|B\cup C)=\frac{{\bf P}(B\cap C)}{{\bf P}(B\cup
C)}=.2/.7=2/7.
\end{displaymath} -->


<IMG
 WIDTH="312" HEIGHT="49"
 SRC="img8.gif"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}{\bf P}(B\cap C\vert B\cup C)=\frac{{\bf P}(B\cap C)}{{\bf P}(B\cup
C)}=.2/.7=2/7.\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P><DT><B>C.</B>
<DD><DT><B>(i)</B>
<DD>Since 
<!-- MATH: ${\bf P}(A\cap B)={\bf P}(B|A){\bf P}(A)=.6*.6$ -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="245" HEIGHT="31" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img9.gif"
 ALT="${\bf P}(A\cap B)={\bf P}(B\vert A){\bf P}(A)=.6*.6$">
we find that
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH: \begin{displaymath}
{\bf P}(\bar{A}\cap\bar{B})=1-{\bf P}(A\cup B)=1-[{\bf P}(A)+{\bf P}(B)-{\bf P}(A\cap B)]=
1-(.6+.5-.6*.6)=.26.
\end{displaymath} -->


<IMG
 WIDTH="555" HEIGHT="38"
 SRC="img10.gif"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}{\bf P}(\bar{A}\cap\bar{B})=1-{\bf P}(A\cup B)=1-[{\bf P}(A)+{\bf P}(B)-{\bf P}(A\cap B)]=
1-(.6+.5-.6*.6)=.26.\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P>
<P>
The different interpretation of this question is possible, so the
full credit is granted also for the following solution:
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH: \begin{displaymath}
{\bf P}(\overline{A\cap B})=1-{\bf P}(A\cap B)=1-.6*.6=.64.
\end{displaymath} -->


<IMG
 WIDTH="318" HEIGHT="38"
 SRC="img11.gif"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}{\bf P}(\overline{A\cap B})=1-{\bf P}(A\cap B)=1-.6*.6=.64.\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P><DT><B>(ii)</B>
<DD>Since the probability that C occurs is independent
of whether A or B occurs  we have that
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH: \begin{displaymath}
{\bf P}(\bar{C}|\bar{A}\cup\bar{B})={\bf P}(\bar{C})=.6.
\end{displaymath} -->


<IMG
 WIDTH="181" HEIGHT="38"
 SRC="img12.gif"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}{\bf P}(\bar{C}\vert\bar{A}\cup\bar{B})={\bf P}(\bar{C})=.6.\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P>
Hence,
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH: \begin{displaymath}
{\bf P}(A\cup B\cup C)=1-{\bf P}(\bar{A}\cap\bar{B}\cap\bar{C})=
1-{\bf P}(\bar{C}|\bar{A}\cap\bar{B}){\bf P}(\bar{A}\cap\bar{B})
\end{displaymath} -->


<IMG
 WIDTH="443" HEIGHT="38"
 SRC="img13.gif"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}{\bf P}(A\cup B\cup C)=1-{\bf P}(\bar{A}\cap\bar{B}\cap\bar{C...
...f P}(\bar{C}\vert\bar{A}\cap\bar{B}){\bf P}(\bar{A}\cap\bar{B})\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P>
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH: \begin{displaymath}
=1-{\bf P}(\bar{C}){\bf P}(\bar{A}\cap\bar{B})=1-.6*.26=.844.
\end{displaymath} -->


<IMG
 WIDTH="298" HEIGHT="38"
 SRC="img14.gif"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}=1-{\bf P}(\bar{C}){\bf P}(\bar{A}\cap\bar{B})=1-.6*.26=.844.\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P></DL>
<P>
<B>Problem III</B>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT><B>A.</B>
<DD>
<!-- MATH: ${\bf P}(\mbox{Find on C})$ -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="101" HEIGHT="31" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img15.gif"
 ALT="${\bf P}(\mbox{Find on C})$">
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH: \begin{displaymath}
\begin{array}{rl}
=&{\bf P}(\mbox{Find on C}|\mbox{Correct submenu on C is chosen
}){\bf P}(\mbox{Correct submenu on C is chosen})\\=&.7*.9=.63.
\end{array}
\end{displaymath} -->

<IMG
 WIDTH="607" HEIGHT="64"
 SRC="img16.gif"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}\begin{array}{rl}
=&{\bf P}(\mbox{Find on C}\vert\mbox{Correc...
...box{Correct submenu on C is chosen})\\ =&.7*.9=.63.
\end{array}\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P><DT><B>B.</B>
<DD>Using previous result we find that
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH: \begin{displaymath}
\begin{array}{rcl}
{\bf P}(\mbox{Find the page})&=&{\bf P}(\mbox{Find the page}|\mbox{A is
chosen}){\bf P}(\mbox{A is chosen})\\&&+{\bf P}(\mbox{Find the
page}|\mbox{B is chosen}){\bf P}(\mbox{B is chosen})\\
&&+{\bf P}(\mbox{Find the page}|\mbox{C is chosen}){\bf P}(\mbox{C is
chosen})\\&=&.5*1/3+.56*1/3+.63*1/3=169/300 =0.56(3).
\end{array}
\end{displaymath} -->


<IMG
 WIDTH="526" HEIGHT="121"
 SRC="img17.gif"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}\begin{array}{rcl}
{\bf P}(\mbox{Find the page})&=&{\bf P}(\m...
...sen})\\ &=&.5*1/3+.56*1/3+.63*1/3=169/300 =0.56(3).
\end{array}\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P><DT><B>C.</B>
<DD>The probability of finding the page on A is .5; for
B this probability is .56; for C it is .63. So search engine C is
best.
<DT><B>D.</B>
<DD>First we note that
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH: \begin{displaymath}
\begin{array}{rcl}
{\bf P}(\mbox{The page is found})&=& {\bf P}(\mbox{A is chosen}\cap\mbox{A
is accessed}\cap\mbox{The page is found on A})\\&&+{\bf P}(\mbox{B is
chosen}\cap\mbox{B is accessed}\cap\mbox{The page is found on
B})\\&&+{\bf P}(\mbox{C is chosen}\cap\mbox{C is
accessed}\cap\mbox{The page is found on C})\\& =&
1/3*1*.5+1/3*.9*.56+1/3*.8*.63=1508/3000=.502(6).
\end{array}
\end{displaymath} -->


<IMG
 WIDTH="648" HEIGHT="121"
 SRC="img18.gif"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}\begin{array}{rcl}
{\bf P}(\mbox{The page is found})&=& {\bf ...
...&
1/3*1*.5+1/3*.9*.56+1/3*.8*.63=1508/3000=.502(6).
\end{array}\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P>
So,
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH: \begin{displaymath}
{\bf P}(\mbox{A is chosen}|\mbox{The page is
found})=\frac{1/3*1*.5}{1/3*1*.5+1/3*.9*.56+1/3*.8*.63}=500/1508.
\end{displaymath} -->


<IMG
 WIDTH="635" HEIGHT="49"
 SRC="img19.gif"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}{\bf P}(\mbox{A is chosen}\vert\mbox{The page is
found})=\frac{1/3*1*.5}{1/3*1*.5+1/3*.9*.56+1/3*.8*.63}=500/1508.\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P></DL><B>Problem IV</B>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT><B>A.</B>
<DD>The probability distribution of <I>X</I> is shown below:
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<TABLE CELLPADDING=3 BORDER="1">
<TR><TD ALIGN="CENTER"><I>X</I></TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">-1000</TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">0</TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">500</TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">1000</TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="CENTER"><IMG
 WIDTH="17" HEIGHT="14" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img20.gif"
 ALT="${\bf P}$"></TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">.1</TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">.2</TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">.2</TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">.5</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE></DIV><DT><B>(i)</B>
<DD>
<!-- MATH: ${\bf P}(X>0)=.2+.5=.7.$ -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="176" HEIGHT="31" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img21.gif"
 ALT="${\bf P}(X>0)=.2+.5=.7.$"><DT><B>(ii)</B>
<DD>
<!-- MATH: ${\bf E}(X)=-1000*.1+0*.2+500*.2+1000*.5=500.$ -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="390" HEIGHT="31" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img22.gif"
 ALT="${\bf E}(X)=-1000*.1+0*.2+500*.2+1000*.5=500.$"><DT><B>(iii)</B>
<DD>
<!-- MATH: ${\bf
Var}(X)=(-1000-500)^2*.1+(0-500)^2*.2+(500-500)^2*.2+(1000-500)^2*.5=400000$ -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="676" HEIGHT="34" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img23.gif"
 ALT="${\bf
Var}(X)=(-1000-500)^2*.1+(0-500)^2*.2+(500-500)^2*.2+(1000-500)^2*.5=400000$">Respectively, standard deviation 
<!-- MATH: $\sigma=\sqrt{400000}$ -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="96" HEIGHT="36" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img24.gif"
 ALT="$\sigma=\sqrt{400000}$">.
<DT><B>B.</B>
<DD><DT><B>(i)</B>
<DD>
<!-- MATH: ${\bf P}(X>0)=\displaystyle\int_0^1(x+1)/2\,dx=x^2/4+x/2\Big|_0^1=3/4.$ -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="362" HEIGHT="57" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img25.gif"
 ALT="${\bf P}(X>0)=\displaystyle\int_0^1(x+1)/2\,dx=x^2/4+x/2\Big\vert _0^1=3/4.$"><DT><B>(ii)</B>
<DD>
<!-- MATH: $\displaystyle{\bf E}(X)=\int_{-1}^1x(x+1)/2\,dx=x^3/6+x^2/4\Big|_{-1}^1=1/3.$ -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="364" HEIGHT="57" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img26.gif"
 ALT="$\displaystyle{\bf E}(X)=\int_{-1}^1x(x+1)/2\,dx=x^3/6+x^2/4\Big\vert _{-1}^1=1/3.$"><DT><B>C.</B>
<DD>The distribution of daily profits, <I>Y</I>, is given by
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<TABLE CELLPADDING=3 BORDER="1">
<TR><TD ALIGN="CENTER"><I>Y</I></TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">-1500</TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">-500</TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">500</TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">1500</TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="CENTER"><IMG
 WIDTH="17" HEIGHT="14" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img20.gif"
 ALT="${\bf P}$"></TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">.1</TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">.2</TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">.2</TD>
<TD ALIGN="CENTER">.5</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE></DIV>
Hence, 
<!-- MATH: ${\bf E}(Y)=-1500*.1+-500*.2+500*.2+1500*.5=600.$ -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="416" HEIGHT="31" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img27.gif"
 ALT="${\bf E}(Y)=-1500*.1+-500*.2+500*.2+1500*.5=600.$">
<P>
</DL>
